In each situation, which number set do you think is most appropriate?

a.  The number of dogs a student has owned throughout their lifetime.

    This number is best considered as a [_]{$whole}{5}.

a.  The difference between the projected annual expenditures and the actual annual expenditures for a given company.

    This number is best considered as a [_]{$rational}{5}.

a.  The length around swimming pool in the shape of a half circle with radius [`10\,\text{ft}\text{.}`]

    This number is best considered as a [_]{$irrational}{5}.

a.  The proportion of students at a college who own a car.

    This number is best considered as a [_]{$rational}{5}.

a.  The width of a sheet of paper, in inches.

    This number is best considered as a [_]{$rational}{5}.

a.  The number of people eating in a non-empty restaurant.

    This number is best considered as a [_]{$natural}{5}.

